= Percentages -- Exercises

+ In a sale, all normal prices are reduced by 20%. In the sale, the normal price of a tablet computer is reduced by $euro 79$. Work out the normal price of the tablet computer. #ans[$euro 395$]

+ In a sale, all normal prices are reduced by 15%. The normal price of a washing machine is 270 dollars. Work out the sale price of the washing machine. #ans[$dollar 229.50$]

+ When Flora has walked 20% of the way from her home to her work, she has 1200 metres more to walk than when she has 20% of the walk remaining. How far, in metres, is it from her home to her work? #ans[2km]

+ In 2003, the population of Great Britain was $6.0 times 10^7$. In 1933 the population of Great Britain was $4.5 times 10^7$. Calculate the percentage increase in the population of Great Britain from 1933 to 2003. Give your answer correct to one decimal place. #ans[33.3%]

+ The value of a boat depreciates by 16% each year. At the end of 2012, the value of the boat is £65000. Work out the value of the boat at the end of 2015. #ans[£38,525.76]

== Challenge Questions

#set enum(numbering: "C1)")

+ Nina increases a number, $x$, by $p%$ and gets the result 105. She then decreases another number which is twice as big as $x$ by $2p%$ and gets the same result. Find $p$ and $x$. #ans[$p = 20%$, $x=87.5$]

+ Ursula claims that $x%$ of $y$ is the same as $y%$ of $x$ for all $x$ and $y$. Show algebraically why Ursula's method works. #ans[$\"x% "of" y\" = x/100 times y = x times y / 100 = \"y% "of" x\"$]
